    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Created during the Franco-German summit at La Rochelle it includes five European nations, referred to as the \"framework nations\". Those are: Belgium, France, Germany, Luxembourg and Spain. Today, a total of 14 nations are represented. In addition to humanitarian activities of the European Union and NATO, the Eurocorps can be deployed for the common defence of the Allies and the maintenance and re-establishment of peace."@en;
