    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The Arab Maghreb Union is a trade agreement aiming for an economic and future political unity among Arab countries of the Maghreb in North Africa. It is composed of the following countries: Algeria, Libya, Mauritania, Morocco and Tunisia."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "COB0001030"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "AMU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "AMU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>;
