    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Europeiska rundradiounionen"@sv, "Ευρωπαϊκή ένωση ραδιοφωνίας"@el, "European Broadcasting Union"@en, "Evropská unie pro rozhlasové vysílání"@cs, "Unjoni Ewropea tax-Xandir"@mt, "Unión Europea de Radiodifusión"@es, "Európai Műsorszolgáltatók Szövetsége"@hu, "Union der Europäischen Rundfunkorganisationen"@de, "Európska únia rozhlasového vysielania"@sk, "Aontas Craolacháin na hEorpa"@ga, "Europska unija za radioteleviziju"@hr, "Euroopan yleisradioliitto"@fi, "Evropska zveza radijskih in televizijskih postaj"@sl, "União Europeia de Radiodifusão"@pt, "Eiropas Raidorganizāciju savienība"@lv, "Uniunea Europeană de Radio și Televiziune"@ro, "Europejska Unia Nadawców"@pl, "Union européenne de radio-télévision"@fr, "Europos transliuotojų sąjunga"@lt, "Европейски съюз за радиоразпръскване"@bg, "Unione europea di radiodiffusione"@it, "Euroopa Ringhäälingute Liit"@et, "Europese Radio-unie"@nl, "Den Europæiske Radiounion"@da;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "L’Union européenne de radio-télévision est une organisation internationale, la plus importante association professionnelle de radiodiffuseurs nationaux dans le monde avec 75 membres actifs dans 56 pays d’Europe, d’Afrique du Nord et du Proche-Orient, et 45 membres associés dans 25 pays d’autres régions du monde."@fr, "The EBU is the world’s largest professional association of national broadcasters, whose Members reach a weekly audience of 650 million people. The EBU’s purpose is to serve and support the interests of its Members, and the values of public service broadcasting, which are central to Members’ activities. The organization provides services to the broadcasting community at large, along with expertise specifically to Members on legal, technical and programming issues. It also conducts economic and market analyses and offers targeted training programmes."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "COB0001280"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "UER"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#FD_050>, "EBU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "EBU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>;
    <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/EBU_1950_0>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/identifier> "EBU";
    <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/op-code> "EBU";
    <http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/authority/op-code> "EBU";
    <http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/authority/start.use> "1950-02-12";
    <http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/authority/authority-code> "EBU";
