    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The International Renewable Energy Agency (IRENA) is an intergovernmental organisation that supports countries in their transition to a sustainable energy future, and serves as the principal platform for international co-operation, a centre of excellence, and a repository of policy, technology, resource and financial knowledge on renewable energy."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "COB0000970"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "IRENA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "IRENA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>;
